RACE.RACE_TEXT: Arabian Claiming Championship S. LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 86. Stakes Purse 43800. FOR ARABIAN THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH MUST HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS TWICE IN 2023 AT ANY TEXAS RACETRACK . No nomination fee. $200 to enter at time of entry and $200 to start. The $40,000 added and all fees to be divided 60% to winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 6% to fourth, and 4% to fifth after sixth through last are paid $1,000 each. Weights: Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Total earnings in 2023 as determined by the information provided by Equibase Co mpany will be used in determining preference of horses. The field will be limited to 14 starters.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUICK RAE AA stalked the battling trio from the inside down the backstretch, then advanced on the turn to gain command at the quarter pole then held clear down the stretch under a strong drive to prove best in the end. KISSOUUR saved ground in the early furlongs, then gained second position leaving the bend but was no match in the end and was best for place. AA TAKE A CHANCE raced in the middle of the field from the inside then bid from the four path leaving the turn but lacked the winning bid in the end. RB RATHOWAYNE settled in the two path early, then rallied in the early stretch but was too little too late. UPTOWN RINGOFFIRE stayed in the gate at the start once again, rallied mildly in the upper stretch and came up empty. FOUR HUNDRED PROOF AA vied for the lead between rivals, was in tight entering the turn, settled back and lacked late bid in the end. FLEET DE SAND vied for the lead while three wide, menaced on the turn closely behind the new leader from the inside before giving way in the stretch. RB MUNCHIE vied from the inside under a hard drive then flattened out on the turn. WMA NORTH WIND raced early from the inside then was finished after the half.
